Notes on Email Etiquette Applied
Both emails follow these professional email rules:

Clear subject line — specific, informative, and relevant (not vague like "Hello" or "Query").
Professional greeting — uses "Dear [Name]," (not "Hey", "Hi there", or no greeting at all).
Structured body — opening context → specific request/purpose → supporting detail → polite close.
Respectful and formal tone — no slang, abbreviations (no "pls", "u", "asap"), or overly casual language.
Proper sign-off — "Warm regards" / "Yours sincerely" followed by full name, designation, and contact details.
No unnecessary length — both emails state the purpose clearly without padding.
